Key Match Events: Immanuel Quickley scored 21 points and made 15 assists after missing the Raptors' last 22 games with a partially torn ulnar collateral ligament in his right elbow.
Scottie Barnes led all scorers with 33 points and 13 rebounds.
Post-Match Reflections: Immanuel Quickley expressed gratitude for being able to compete again after his injury.
Quickley emphasized the importance of building a culture of winning, enthusiasm, joy, and unselfishness within the team.
Head coach Darko Rajakovic praised Quickley's skills and his role as an extension of the coach on the floor.
Scottie Barnes highlighted RJ Barrett's ability to drive the ball and take pressure off his teammates, making the team more dangerous.
Quickley noted that RJ Barrett's defensive improvements would be crucial for the team moving forward.
